orld Cup win, with Iran and Belgium on 2 and New Zealand on 1. Group H has Spain clear on 4, then Uruguay and Cape Verde level on 2 (Uruguay second on goals scored) and Saudi Arabia on 1. No new player reached two goals, so the top-scorers list is unchanged (Messi and David still lead the Golden Boot race on 3). The Monday Jun 22 games had not started at refresh time and were left pending. NEWS rotated to five fresh, multi-source stories: Cape Verde's fairytale and first-ever World Cup goals denying Uruguay (ESPN/Al Jazeera/NBC); keeper Vozinha's viral 14M-follower breakout (ESPN/Yahoo); Iran's 'beautiful game in worst conditions' amid same-night U.S. exits and a FIFA complaint (ESPN/Al Jazeera/CBS); the hydration-break backlash (Yahoo/ESPN/Al Jazeera); and climate scientists' heat warnings across host venues (Climate Central/Scientific American/Al Jazeera)."}}